      "value": "<p>@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.R1ew21i3luHJHfV5]{UM5 Ch.6: Gear} @Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-equipment.lmAMoPPYbIwgHfGl]{Battry Cell, Medium}</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Laser sights may be used in conjunction with scopes. They paint targets with precision where the weaponâ€™s fire will strike. This also doubles as a psychological attack, as most individuals find a green target on their chest to be a great incentive to negotiation. A sniper may, if they wish, swap it for an infrared diode, which is invisible to everything except for night vision (darkvision). The standard sight uses a green diode solid-state laser that is effective for the maximum range of any weapon. You gain a +1 bonus to your first attack roll on each turn.<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">&nbsp;</span></p>",
